# Framework Entrypoint & Core Rule Index

This document serves as a central index for essential rule documents within the framework.

## 1. Core Framework Directives

*   **System Overview & Global Mandates:** [system.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/system.mdc) (Objectives, Operational Model, Mandates)
*   **Framework Engine & Agent Turn Protocol:** [loop.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/loop.mdc) (Engine, Mandatory Procedures)
*   **Core Concepts & Terminology:** [concepts.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/concepts.mdc) (Glossary)
*   **Ultra-Deep Thinking Protocol:** [protocol.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/protocol.mdc) (`ProjectManager` strategic planning, verification, analysis)
*   **Initialization Procedure:** [init.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/init.mdc) (`SeedingAgent` for `.cursor/rules/` setup)
*   **Framework Entrypoint & Core Rule Index:** This document ([entrypoint.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/entrypoint.mdc))

## 2. Agent & Tool Directives

*   **Agent Role Definitions:**
    *   **Registry:** [roles.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/roles.mdc) (Master list and summaries)
    *   **Specifications:** `rules-md/agents/` directory (Primary agent directives)

## 3. Operational Mandates

*   Agents **MUST** fetch their own role specification at the commencement of each turn.
*   Agents **MUST** adhere to the operational model defined in [concepts.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/concepts.mdc) (including [system.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/system.mdc) mandates and [loop.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/loop.mdc) loop), unless explicitly overridden by their role file.
*   This document, [entrypoint.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/entrypoint.mdc), **MUST** be used as a primary index for core rule documents.

> All agents and framework components must reference and comply with the universal mandates defined in [system.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/system.mdc).

